Parliament, Tuesday, 19 June 2018 – The Ad Hoc Committee on the Funding of Political Parties will tomorrow (20 June 2018) hold public hearings on the Political Party Funding Bill. Eight of the eleven interested parties that submitted written comments indicated their willingness to make oral presentations. They are: Counsel for the Advancement of the South African Constitution, South African National Editors Forum, Congress of South African Trade Unions, My Vote Counts, Free Market Foundation, Right-to-Know, Corruption Watch and Economic Freedom Fighters. Details of the public hearings are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 20 June 2018
	Venue: Old Assembly Chamber
	Time: 14:00-17:55 ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE ON THE FUNDING OF POLITICAL PARTIES, MR DIKGANG STOCK For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact committee’s media officer: Name: Mr Justice Molafo
	Tel: 021 403 8444
	Cell: 081 424 7481
	Email: jmolafo@parliament.gov.za A joint committee of Parliament receives submissions on constitutional matters and has to review the Constitution at least once a year.Read more